<servinfosub id = "AENBP70A1706002004" page = "2">
<title>
Fuel Tank Filler Hose
</title>
<topic id = "AENBP70A1706002005">
<title>
Disconnection
</title>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Remove fuel filler cap.
</ptxt>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Insert hose of hand operated pump into fuel tank through fuel filler neck.
</ptxt>
<attention2>
<ptxt>
The hose of the hand-operated pump could damage the fuel tank inlet valve if too much force is applied when inserting or removing it from the fuel tank.
</ptxt>
<ptxt>
Do not apply strong force when inserting or removing the hose of the hand-operated pump.
</ptxt>
</attention2>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Pump out fuel in space “a” shown in figure.
</ptxt>
<attention1>
<ptxt>
There is a risk of fire or explosion due to static electricity if the drained fuel is stored in an open container or plastic container.
</ptxt>
<ptxt>
Store the fuel in a sealed metal container.
</ptxt>
</attention1>
<figure>
<graphic graphicname = "IBP70A170006.swf" width = "88.000mm" height = "26.327mm" ver = "01" gw = "164" gh = "58"/>
<callout>
<table frame = "all" colsep = "1" rowsep = "1">
<tgroup cols = "2" colsep = "1" rowsep = "1">
<colspec colnum = "1" colname = "1" colwidth = "0.315in"/>
<colspec colnum = "2" colname = "2" colwidth = "1.968in"/>
<tbody>
<row rowsep = "0">
<entry colname = "1" border-top = "1" border-bottom = "1" border-left = "1" border-right = "0" align = "right">
<ptxt>
1.
</ptxt>
</entry>
<entry colname = "2" border-top = "1" border-bottom = "1" border-left = "0" border-right = "1" align = "left">
<ptxt>
Fuel tank filler hose
</ptxt>
</entry>
</row>
</tbody>
</tgroup>
</table>
</callout>
</figure>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Remove hose of hand operated pump from fuel filler neck.
</ptxt>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Hoist vehicle.
</ptxt>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Loosen clamp (1) of fuel filler neck side and clamp (2) of fuel tank side.
</ptxt>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Disconnect fuel tank filler hose (4) at fuel filler neck while temporarily placing a fuel filler neck side clamp on fuel filler neck (3).
</ptxt>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Remove fuel tank filler hose along with fuel tank side clamp.
</ptxt>
<figure>
<graphic graphicname = "IBP70A170007.swf" width = "88.000mm" height = "54.729mm" ver = "01" gw = "192" gh = "139"/>
</figure>
</s1>
</topic>
<topic id = "AENBP70A1706002006" page = "2">
<title>
Connection
</title>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Temporarily fit fuel tank side clamp to fuel tank filler hose.
</ptxt>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Install fuel tank filler hose (1) to fuel tank (2).
</ptxt>
<attention3>
<ptxt>
Install the fuel tank filler hose with identification marks on the hose end facing up (approximately).
</ptxt>
</attention3>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Position fuel tank side clamp (3) as specified.
</ptxt>
<spec>
<title>
Clearance “b” between fuel tank and fuel tank filler hose clamp:
</title>
<ptxt>
5 – 10 mm (0.20 – 0.39 in.)
</ptxt>
</spec>
<spec>
<title>
Position range “e” for center of clamp screw thread:
</title>
<ptxt>
45 &#176;
</ptxt>
</spec>
<figure>
<graphic graphicname = "IBP70A170008.swf" width = "88.000mm" height = "63.744mm" ver = "01" gw = "238" gh = "164"/>
</figure>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Pull band part (1) of fuel tank side clamp in direction of arrow with your finger so that it is placed in parallel to the bolt part (2).
</ptxt>
<figure>
<graphic graphicname = "IBP70A170009.swf" width = "88.000mm" height = "68.648mm" ver = "01" gw = "206" gh = "178"/>
</figure>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Tighten fuel tank side clamp (1) until length “a” reaches specified value.
</ptxt>
<spec>
<title>
Protruding length “a” of band part of clamp:
</title>
<ptxt>
13 – 17 mm (0.51 – 0.67 in.)
</ptxt>
</spec>
<figure>
<graphic graphicname = "IBP70A170010.swf" width = "88.000mm" height = "63.977mm" ver = "01" gw = "212" gh = "165"/>
</figure>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Push band part (1) in arrow direction with finger and put it back.
</ptxt>
<figure>
<graphic graphicname = "IBP70A170011.swf" width = "88.000mm" height = "63.000mm" ver = "01" gw = "212" gh = "162"/>
</figure>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Rotate plastic clamp (1) in arrow direction.
</ptxt>
<figure>
<graphic graphicname = "IBP70A170012.swf" width = "88.000mm" height = "57.178mm" ver = "01" gw = "191" gh = "146"/>
</figure>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Apply white gasoline or kerosene to all around the outer circumference of fuel tank filler hose attachment section of the fuel filler neck.
</ptxt>
<attention4>
<ptxt>
Remaining lint from cloth may cause fuel leakage.
</ptxt>
<ptxt>
Use lint-free cloth to apply white gasoline or kerosene.
</ptxt>
</attention4>
<attention3>
<ptxt>
Apply white gasoline or kerosene to insert fuel tank filler hose into proper position.
</ptxt>
</attention3>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Push fuel tank filler hose (1) straight into fuel filler neck (not at an angle) until fuel tank filler hose end passes over the spool (3) on fuel filler neck (2).
</ptxt>
<figure>
<graphic graphicname = "IBP70A170013.swf" width = "88.000mm" height = "59.920mm" ver = "01" gw = "204" gh = "153"/>
<callout>
<table frame = "all" colsep = "1" rowsep = "1">
<tgroup cols = "2" colsep = "1" rowsep = "1">
<colspec colnum = "1" colname = "1" colwidth = "0.315in"/>
<colspec colnum = "2" colname = "2" colwidth = "1.968in"/>
<tbody>
<row rowsep = "0">
<entry colname = "1" border-top = "1" border-bottom = "1" border-left = "1" border-right = "0" align = "right">
<ptxt>
4.
</ptxt>
</entry>
<entry colname = "2" border-top = "1" border-bottom = "1" border-left = "0" border-right = "1" align = "left">
<ptxt>
Bulge
</ptxt>
</entry>
</row>
</tbody>
</tgroup>
</table>
</callout>
</figure>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
While pushing fuel tank filler hose (1) by hand to keep it fully inserted, make a mark (3) at hose end on fuel filler neck (2).
</ptxt>
<figure>
<graphic graphicname = "IBP70A170014.swf" width = "88.000mm" height = "61.482mm" ver = "01" gw = "207" gh = "158"/>
</figure>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Release hand and check that there is a clearance (4) between mark (3) and fuel tank filler hose end (1). Further, check that the hose end is positioned over the spool on the fuel filler neck (2).
</ptxt>
<figure>
<graphic graphicname = "IBP70A170015.swf" width = "88.000mm" height = "64.519mm" ver = "01" gw = "208" gh = "166"/>
</figure>
<attention3>
<list1 type = "unordered">
<item>
<ptxt>
If the clearance does not appear, erase the mark. Then, recheck clearance repeating steps 10) and 11).
</ptxt>
</item>
<item>
<ptxt>
Clearance appears when the hose moves by its contraction after releasing the hand. Slight movement will be enough to create a clearance.
</ptxt>
</item>
<item>
<ptxt>
Refer to the following illustration for fuel tank filler hose positioning.
</ptxt>
</item>
<item>
<ptxt>
Apply white gasoline or kerosene to insert fuel tank filler hose into proper position.
</ptxt>
</item>
</list1>
</attention3>
<ptxt>
<emph etype = "bold">
Fuel tank filler hose end position OK
</emph>
</ptxt>
<figure>
<graphic graphicname = "IBP70A170016.swf" width = "88.000mm" height = "46.247mm" ver = "01" gw = "133" gh = "115"/>
</figure>
<ptxt>
<emph etype = "bold">
Fuel tank filler hose end position not OK
</emph>
</ptxt>
<figure>
<graphic graphicname = "IBP70A170017.swf" width = "88.000mm" height = "46.247mm" ver = "01" gw = "133" gh = "115"/>
<callout>
<table frame = "all" colsep = "1" rowsep = "1">
<tgroup cols = "4" colsep = "1" rowsep = "1">
<colspec colnum = "1" colname = "1" colwidth = "0.315in"/>
<colspec colnum = "2" colname = "2" colwidth = "1.326in"/>
<colspec colnum = "3" colname = "3" colwidth = "0.315in"/>
<colspec colnum = "4" colname = "4" colwidth = "1.326in"/>
<tbody>
<row rowsep = "1">
<entry colname = "1" border-top = "1" border-bottom = "1" border-left = "1" border-right = "0" align = "right">
<ptxt>
1.
</ptxt>
</entry>
<entry colname = "2" border-top = "1" border-bottom = "1" border-left = "0" border-right = "1" align = "left">
<ptxt>
Hose end position
</ptxt>
</entry>
<entry colname = "3" border-top = "1" border-bottom = "1" border-left = "1" border-right = "0" align = "right">
<ptxt>
4.
</ptxt>
</entry>
<entry colname = "4" border-top = "1" border-bottom = "1" border-left = "0" border-right = "1" align = "left">
<ptxt>
Bulge
</ptxt>
</entry>
</row>
<row rowsep = "1">
<entry colname = "1" border-top = "1" border-bottom = "1" border-left = "1" border-right = "0" align = "right">
<ptxt>
2.
</ptxt>
</entry>
<entry colname = "2" border-top = "1" border-bottom = "1" border-left = "0" border-right = "1" align = "left">
<ptxt>
Fuel filler neck
</ptxt>
</entry>
<entry colname = "3" border-top = "1" border-bottom = "1" border-left = "1" border-right = "0" align = "right">
<ptxt>
5.
</ptxt>
</entry>
<entry colname = "4" border-top = "1" border-bottom = "1" border-left = "0" border-right = "1" align = "left">
<ptxt>
Spool
</ptxt>
</entry>
</row>
<row rowsep = "0">
<entry colname = "1" border-top = "1" border-bottom = "1" border-left = "1" border-right = "0" align = "right">
<ptxt>
3.
</ptxt>
</entry>
<entry colname = "2" border-top = "1" border-bottom = "1" border-left = "0" border-right = "1" align = "left">
<ptxt>
Fuel filler hose
</ptxt>
</entry>
<entry colname = "3" border-top = "1" border-bottom = "1" border-left = "1" border-right = "0" align = "right">
<ptxt>
</ptxt>
</entry>
<entry colname = "4" border-top = "1" border-bottom = "1" border-left = "0" border-right = "1" align = "left">
<ptxt>
</ptxt>
</entry>
</row>
</tbody>
</tgroup>
</table>
</callout>
</figure>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Install clamp (1) of fuel filler neck side just between spool and bulge (arrow portions) on the fuel tank filler hose.
</ptxt>
<figure>
<graphic graphicname = "IBP70A170018.swf" width = "88.000mm" height = "58.804mm" ver = "01" gw = "120" gh = "150"/>
</figure>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Hold fuel filler neck side clamp straight by hand at the center between spool and bulge and specified angle.
</ptxt>
<spec>
<title>
Position range “e” for center of clamp screw thread:
</title>
<ptxt>
45 &#176;
</ptxt>
</spec>
<figure>
<graphic graphicname = "IBP70A170019.swf" width = "88.000mm" height = "77.822mm" ver = "01" gw = "207" gh = "204"/>
<callout>
<table frame = "all" colsep = "1" rowsep = "1">
<tgroup cols = "4" colsep = "1" rowsep = "1">
<colspec colnum = "1" colname = "1" colwidth = "0.315in"/>
<colspec colnum = "2" colname = "2" colwidth = "1.343in"/>
<colspec colnum = "3" colname = "3" colwidth = "0.315in"/>
<colspec colnum = "4" colname = "4" colwidth = "1.343in"/>
<tbody>
<row rowsep = "0">
<entry colname = "1" border-top = "1" border-bottom = "1" border-left = "1" border-right = "0" align = "right">
<ptxt>
[A]:
</ptxt>
</entry>
<entry colname = "2" border-top = "1" border-bottom = "1" border-left = "0" border-right = "1" align = "left">
<ptxt>
Upper side
</ptxt>
</entry>
<entry colname = "3" border-top = "1" border-bottom = "1" border-left = "1" border-right = "0" align = "right">
<ptxt>
[B]:
</ptxt>
</entry>
<entry colname = "4" border-top = "1" border-bottom = "1" border-left = "0" border-right = "1" align = "left">
<ptxt>
Lower side
</ptxt>
</entry>
</row>
</tbody>
</tgroup>
</table>
</callout>
</figure>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Tighten clamp (1) of fuel filler neck side until length “d” reaches specified value.
</ptxt>
<spec>
<title>
Protruding length “d” of screw thread:
</title>
<ptxt>
8 – 12 mm (0.32 – 0.47 in.)
</ptxt>
</spec>
<figure>
<graphic graphicname = "IBP70A170020.swf" width = "88.000mm" height = "60.330mm" ver = "01" gw = "204" gh = "155"/>
</figure>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Visually check bulge on fuel tank filler hose. Repeat step 10) if check result is not as specified.
</ptxt>
<ptxt>
<emph etype = "bold">
Fuel tank filler hose bulge is in good shape
</emph>
</ptxt>
<ptxt>
<emph etype = "bold">
Bulge “A” = “B”: In uniform contact with pipe 
</emph>
</ptxt>
<figure>
<graphic graphicname = "IBP70A170021.swf" width = "88.000mm" height = "59.334mm" ver = "01" gw = "211" gh = "152"/>
</figure>
<ptxt>
<emph etype = "bold">
Fuel tank filler hose bulge is not in good shape
</emph>
</ptxt>
<ptxt>
<emph etype = "bold">
Bulge “C”: In excess contact with pipe
</emph>
</ptxt>
<ptxt>
<emph etype = "bold">
Bulge “D”: In poor contact with pipe
</emph>
</ptxt>
<figure>
<graphic graphicname = "IBP70A170022.swf" width = "88.000mm" height = "57.924mm" ver = "01" gw = "210" gh = "148"/>
</figure>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Turn the plastic clamp so that its direction [A] becomes parallel to line [B] of rear axle (1), and clamp the hoses.
</ptxt>
<figure>
<graphic graphicname = "IBP70A170023.swf" width = "88.000mm" height = "58.256mm" ver = "01" gw = "193" gh = "149"/>
</figure>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Lower vehicle.
</ptxt>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
If fuel is drained, return fuel to fuel tank.
</ptxt>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Install fuel filler cap.
</ptxt>
</s1>
</topic>
